      "description": "Solid project or budget daily with strong bones and plenty of upside. The powertrain pulls well, the drivetrain feels mechanically intact, and it has the kind of honest wear you\u2019d expect from a car that\u2019s been used rather than neglected. A good candidate for someone who wants dependable basic transportation, a weekend fixer, or a platform to sort and improve over time. Not perfect cosmetically, but it presents as a usable, straightforward car with value where it counts.",
